## 6. C++ Implementation

```cpp
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

struct Node {
    int data;
    Node* left;
    Node* right;

    Node(int val) {
        data = val;        // node ka value store kar rahe hain
        left = NULL;       // left child initially NULL
        right = NULL;      // right child initially NULL
    }
};

void inorder(Node* root) {
    if (root == NULL) {
        return;  // agar node nahi hai to wapas aa jao
    }

    inorder(root->left);   // step 1: left subtree visit karo
    cout << root->data << " "; // step 2: root print karo
    inorder(root->right);  // step 3: right subtree visit karo
}

int main() {
    // tree bana rahe hain
    Node* root = new Node(1);
    root->left = new Node(2);
    root->right = new Node(3);

    inorder(root); // inorder traversal call

    return 0;
}
```

---

### Code Line-by-Line Meaning (Simple)

* `Node* left/right` → left aur right child ke pointers
* `if (root == NULL)` → base case (stop condition)
* `inorder(root->left)` → left side pe jao
* `cout << root->data` → node print karo
* `inorder(root->right)` → right side pe jao

